The paper deals with online matching problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and game theory. The use of metric spaces suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the optimization aspect of minimizing the sum of distances and time intervals suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on competitive analysis and the development of new algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT).
